        <p>This is a simple editor that you can use  to view and modify the <MadCap:keyword term="True code" />true code, including text, tags, and <MadCap:keyword term="Metadata" />metadata<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> in HTM files</MadCap:conditionalText>. There is no requirement to use the Internal Text Editor at all. Those who are new to <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> will usually work in the regular user interface views, but those who are more advanced will probably find the Internal Text Editor to be quite useful. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">Most of the files in your project can be opened and modified in the Internal Text Editor by right-clicking the file and selecting <span class="Emphasis">Open with&gt;Internal Text Editor</span>. The XML Editor includes a tab at the bottom to access the Internal Text Editor. For topic and snippet files, this editor also lets you show or hide line numbers, collapse or expand tagged areas (outlines), show or hide syntax coloring, and wrap text.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
